description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF contributed to training 744 peer educators and 135 facilitators on prevention of HIV / AIDS and sexually transmitted infections and child marriage, bringing the number of active young peer educators in the 27-active youth centres to 1,815. Young people and adolescents aged 10 to 24 years benefited from information on AIDS, gender-based violence and child marriage and 155,367 young people and adolescents aged 10 to 19 years, including 70,326 girls (45.2 per cent) and 85,041 boys (54.7 per cent) were tested and received their results, based on the Reading and Cultural Animation youth centers Database, September 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/02/2020
